  "text": "One of the promising approaches to cope with NP-hardness in solving DO problems is the construction of decomposition methods [CITATION_1] . Decomposition techniques usually determine subproblems the solutions of which can be combined to create a solution of the initial DO problem. Usually, DO problems from applications have a special structure, and the matrices of constraints for large-scale problems have a lot of zero elements (sparse matrices). The nonzero elements of the matrix often fall into a limited number of blocks. The block form of many DO problems is usually caused by the weak connectedness of subsystems of real-world systems.",
